# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:101
msgid "Aspect Ratio"
msgstr "Sideforhold"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:101
msgid ""
"The aspect ratio of the final exported video. 1920×1080 reduces to 16:9. "
"This also takes into account the pixel ratio, for example 2:1 rectangular "
"pixels will affect the aspect ratio."
msgstr ""
"Sideforholdet til den endelige eksporterte videoen. 1920×1080 tilsvarer "
"16:9. Dette tar også hensyn til pikselforholdet, for eksempel vil 2:1 "
"rektangulære piksler påvirke sideforholdet."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:102
msgid "Pixel Ratio"
msgstr "Pikselforhold"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:102
msgid ""
"The ratio representing pixel shape. Most video profiles use a 1:1 square "
"pixel shape, but others will use rectangular pixels."
msgstr ""
"Forholdet som representerer pikselens form. De fleste videoprofiler bruker "
"en 1:1 kvadratisk pikselform, men andre bruker rektangulære piksler."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:103
msgid "Frame Rate"
msgstr "Bildefrekvens"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:103
msgid "The frequency that the frames will be displayed at."
msgstr "Frekvensen som bildene vises med."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:104
msgid "Interlaced"
msgstr "Interlaced"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:104
msgid ""
"Is this format used on alternating scan lines (i.e. broadcast and analog "
"formats)"
msgstr ""
"Er dette formatet brukt på vekslende skannelinjer (f.eks. kringkasting og "
"analoge formater)"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:105
msgid "Spherical"
msgstr "Sfærisk"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../export.rst:105
msgid ""
"When enabled, injects spherical 360° metadata (SV3D atom) into the exported "
"file so compatible players immediately recognize it as a 360° video."
msgstr ""
"Når aktivert, injiserer sfærisk 360° metadata (SV3D-atom) i den eksporterte "
"filen slik at kompatible spillere umiddelbart gjenkjenner den som en 360° "
"video."

